rComments: I loved Melissa's class. She talked a lot about her kids during class, which made some topics memorable.

There were a lot of group project, i think over 50% of your grades were base on group project, and 4 short reading quiz. If you love doing group project you would love this class. The final is take home and apply the concept which was great. She tries to make the material applicable to our everyday life. Overall, lots of work for 100 level class
She's kind of biased to people she likes in class for arbitrary reasons. Has weird expectations and grades strangely. Plus, the subject matter of her class is kind of dull.
